metadata.name: Dashboard #74
Collapse #59
metadata.description:
The Impossibility of Representing Something Spherical Flat

A sphere collapses to a flat plane, revealing the transformations and stretching required for such an operation. How to represent something spherical flat? How to see what's not there, or how to see it differently? 

Released on the occasion of the Tribute to Herbert W. Franke.  
50% of the primary sales will be donated to the Foundation Herbert W. Franke.

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 3 #151
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ - Iteration 1, ____ - Iteration 2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Meraviglia #497
metadata.description: Meraviglia is the sentiment of the generative artist when he creates something that with normal tools he would have never created. The unexpected shows up in front of his eyes and an astonished sentiment arises.

metadata.name: Daydreamer #126
metadata.description:
‘For the artist communication with nature remains the most essential condition. The artist is human, himself nature; part of nature within natural space.’ (Paul Klee, 1944) 


Working on long-form nature has an interesting side effect. On the one hand, you're attempting a shallow imitation of a landscape.... You are working with cold logic and code, vainly trying to control randomness to create this virtual facsimile, something you know is artificial.... 

....and yet.... even with all this left-brain activity, your right-brain pushes back, and imagines being there. While working on this project I found myself continually daydreaming, wandering off to hear the sounds of waterfalls, or the crunch of walking along a sandy lake shore. If you've ever wondered about coding, I urge you to learn. Daydreams await....


Press '1' once rendering is finished, to redraw at 5120x5120 resolution 
Press '2' to export without post-processing effects 

3rd party libraries (license text and links included in source) 
- p5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 
- WebGLImageFilter, Dominic Szablewski - phoboslab.org 

I have tried to use soft blurs and shadows to give a sense of layering and depth to the scene. After viewing for a while, it reminds me of 3D paper-art. There are traits for colour and amount of birds, waterfalls, etc. but none are especially rare – These properties are intended for filtering the collection.

metadata.name: fREEDOM PUNK #39
metadata.description:
Welcome to fREEDOM PUNK world.
This project is Image Composition Layers pngs.
Created with 128x128 px format.
There are 9 Layers in this project. (included transparent png files)
- Background > 130 different images
- Body > 12 different body colors.
- Eyes > 24 different eyes.
- Nose > 13 different noses.
- Mouth > 58 different mouths.
- Eyeglasses > 19 different eyeglasses. (chance of nothing is much higher)
- Hair > 133 different hair-styles and headwear.
- Cloth > 160 different clothes.
- Things (In front of the punk) > 60 different things. (chance of nothing is much higher)

So you can generate your unique fREEDOM PUNKs for sure, due to very high possibilities by the layers.

Enjoy and good luck!

metadata.name: The Fire Within #216
metadata.description:
This project is a study of ink, everything is generated in code without using any texture. 
It is an attempt to capture the ink bleeding effect and the look of the traditional Chinese paintings that have texts on top with modern approaches.

metadata.name: Appropriate Hidden Breeze #263
metadata.description:
"Appropriate Hidden Breeze" is a study of blending gradients on a grid. 

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size 12x12" @ 300 DPI

metadata.name: FxPlanet #171
metadata.description:
🟢〰Storyline〰🟢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔴〰Rarity〰🔴

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
◼ The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
◼ For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
◼ Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔵〰Social〰🔵

◼ Participant in events or get achievements to win some prizes.
So it's significant to see you on the discord server. Checkout rarity table, achievements rewards, … on the webpage.
📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🟠〰Interact〰🟠

◼ You can rotate around of planets by “WASD” keys on the keyboard or arrow keys.
◼ Zoom In by “E” key and Zoom Out by “Q”.
◼ Full HD texture by Key “1”.
◼ 4k texture by Key “2”.
◼ 8k texture by Key “3”.
